Benefits of hanging knee raises:
1️⃣ Increases muscular development of ab, oblique and hip flexor muscles. Enhances muscle growth and builds a solid foundation for more complex movements.
2️⃣ Improves midline stability to protect your spine from rotational forces.
3️⃣ Helps improve gymnastic progressions or calisthenic type movements (pull ups, rings dips, muscle ups, etc.).
4️⃣ Improves bracing capacity to help with breathing and contraction of your core muscles performed when lifting.

It’s Monday.. let’s get STRONG 🤩💥💪🏼 

Soooo, are you team SUMO deadlifts or CONVENTIONAL deadlifts!?! 

The DL is an incredibly functional movement… how many times a day do we bend over and pick something up off the ground? 

Deadlifts engage all the major muscle groups, including your back, arms, glutes, quads, hamstrings, and core. 

Sumo & conventional DLs are both VERY effective and work in different ways.

⭐️ BENEFITS OF SDL ⤵️
↠ Sumo stance can offer many individuals a better pulling approach based on hip structure, mobility, and comfort.
↠ Engages more of your vastus muscles (quads) and gluteus maximus leading to increase development. 
↠ When done properly, the SDL can produce less stress on the spinal extensors vs the conventional DL.

My current training routine ⤵️

I LOVE CrossFit and I also LOVE bodybuilding. So… I typically mix these 2 together throughout the week.

Coming from a CrossFit background (which hits every muscle), I tend to lean towards a “full body” bodybuilding regimen which hits everything versus regular body-part splits. It’s also a lot more fun in my opinion 😍

Here’s what yesterdays training looked like:

Back: 6-8 Barbell Rows (Supinated Grip)
Rest 2min. Repeat for 3 total sets.

Biceps: 8-10 Supinated DB Curls.
Rest 90sec. Repeat for 3 total sets.

Chest: 15-20 High Banded Fly’s on each arm. 
Rest 90sec after 2nd arm. Repeat for 3 total sets. 

Shoulders: 6-8 Single Arm Arnold Press on each arm.
Rest 90sec after 2nd arm. Repeat for 3 total sets.

Triceps: 1min of Lee Priest Tricep Extensions
1min rest. Repeat for 3 total sets.

Abs: 5min for max reps of weight Knee Tucks (5-10lbs). 

Front Squat
Set 1) 3 reps @70% of 1RM
Set 2) 3 reps @80% of 1RM
Set 3) MAX reps @90% of 1RM
